  <!-- 1. ANATOMY -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-anatomy">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">🫀</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">Heart Anatomy — Structure</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">تشريح القلب — البنية</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--purple-light);color:var(--purple);">ANATOMY</span>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box blue">
      <div class="def-en">Hollow muscular organ in the center of the thorax (mediastinum), resting on the diaphragm. Weight ≈ <strong>300g</strong>. Function: pumps blood to tissues, supplying O₂ and nutrients.</div>
      <div class="def-ar">عضو عضلي مجوف في وسط الصدر (المنصف)، يستقر على الحجاب الحاجز. الوزن ≈ ٣٠٠جم. يضخ الدم للأنسجة بالأكسجين والغذاء.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="study-grid">
      <div class="s-card"><div class="s-card-num">Endocardium</div><div class="s-card-en">Inner lining of the heart</div><div class="s-card-ar">الطبقة الداخلية للقلب</div><div class="s-card-desc">Lines all cardiac chambers and valves. Smooth surface allows blood to flow without clotting.</div></div>
      <div class="s-card"><div class="s-card-num">Myocardium</div><div class="s-card-en">Middle muscular layer — the PUMP</div><div class="s-card-ar">الطبقة العضلية الوسطى — المضخة</div><div class="s-card-desc">The actual pumping muscle. Thickest in the left ventricle (highest pressure).</div></div>
      <div class="s-card"><div class="s-card-num">Epicardium</div><div class="s-card-en">Outer layer of the heart wall</div><div class="s-card-ar">الطبقة الخارجية لجدار القلب</div><div class="s-card-desc">Visceral layer of the pericardium. Contains coronary vessels and nerves.</div></div>
      <div class="s-card"><div class="s-card-num">Pericardium</div><div class="s-card-en">Thin fibrous sac surrounding the heart</div><div class="s-card-ar">التامور — الكيس الليفي المحيط بالقلب</div><div class="s-card-desc">Pericardial space ≈ <strong>20 mL</strong> fluid → lubricates and reduces friction during systole (contraction).</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box gold" style="margin-top:13px;">
      <div class="def-en">🫀 4 Chambers: Right Atrium → Right Ventricle (pulmonary circuit) · Left Atrium → Left Ventricle (systemic circuit). 4 Valves: Tricuspid · Pulmonic · Mitral (bicuspid) · Aortic.</div>
      <div class="def-ar">٤ حجرات: أذين أيمن → بطين أيمن (الدورة الرئوية) · أذين أيسر → بطين أيسر (الدورة الجهازية). ٤ صمامات: ثلاثي الشرف · رئوي · تاجي · أبهري.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 2. CORONARY -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-coronary">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">🩸</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">Coronary Arteries</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">الشرايين التاجية</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--red-light);color:var(--red);">CORONARY</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="study-list">
      <li><span class="li-icon">🔴</span><div>Left and right coronary arteries supply arterial blood to the heart. They originate from the <strong>aorta just above the aortic valve</strong>.</div></li>
      <li><span class="li-icon">⏰</span><div>Coronary arteries are perfused during <strong>DIASTOLE</strong> (unlike other arteries which perfuse during systole).</div></li>
      <li><span class="li-icon">💓</span><div><strong>Tachycardia (>100 bpm)</strong> → shortened diastole → ↓ coronary perfusion time → <strong>ischemia risk</strong>, especially in CAD patients.</div></li>
      <li><span class="li-icon">🌿</span><div>5 major branches: Left main · Circumflex · Right coronary · Posterior descending · Left Anterior Descending (<strong>LAD</strong>) — "widow maker."</div></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="def-box red" style="margin-top:13px;">
      <div class="def-en">⚠️ Normal HR (60–80 bpm) → adequate diastolic time → adequate coronary perfusion. Tachycardia shortens diastole → reduces time for coronary filling → myocardial ischemia.</div>
      <div class="def-ar">⚠️ معدل قلب طبيعي (٦٠–٨٠) → وقت انبساط كافٍ → تروية كافية. التسارع يقصّر الانبساط → يقلل امتلاء الشرايين التاجية → نقص تروية عضلة القلب.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 3. CAD -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-cad">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">🔬</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">CAD & Atherosclerosis</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">مرض الشريان التاجي وتصلب الشرايين</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--orange-light);color:var(--orange);">CAD</span>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box orange">
      <div class="def-en"><strong>CAD = most prevalent cardiovascular disease in adults.</strong> Caused by atherosclerosis = abnormal accumulation of lipids + fibrous tissue in arterial walls → narrows coronary vessels → ↓ blood flow to myocardium.</div>
      <div class="def-ar"><strong>CAD = أكثر أمراض القلب شيوعاً عند البالغين.</strong> بسبب تصلب الشرايين = تراكم غير طبيعي للدهون والأنسجة الليفية في جدران الشرايين → تضييق → ↓ تدفق الدم للقلب.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-card a"><h4>🔥 Atherosclerosis Process</h4><ul class="care-list" style="margin-top:4px;"><li>Repetitive inflammatory response to artery wall injury</li><li>Lipid + fibrous plaque accumulates (atheroma)</li><li>Vessel lumen narrows → ↓ blood flow</li><li>Plaque rupture → thrombus → complete occlusion = MI</li></ul><p class="ar">تصلب الشرايين: استجابة التهابية متكررة → تراكم لوحة دهنية ليفية → تضييق → تمزق اللوحة → جلطة → احتشاء.</p></div>
      <div class="col-card b"><h4>📊 What Narrows the Vessel</h4><ul class="care-list" style="margin-top:4px;"><li>Lipid deposits (cholesterol, LDL)</li><li>Fibrous tissue accumulation</li><li>Smooth muscle cell proliferation</li><li>Calcium deposits (calcified plaque)</li></ul><p class="ar">ما يضيّق الوعاء: ترسبات دهنية + أنسجة ليفية + تكاثر خلايا عضلية ملساء + كالسيوم.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 4. RISK FACTORS -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-risk">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">⚠️</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">Risk Factors for CAD</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">عوامل خطر مرض الشريان التاجي</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--gold-light);color:var(--orange);">RISK</span>
    </div>
    <table class="idx-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Factors</th><th class="ar-cell">العوامل</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong style="color:var(--red);">Non-Modifiable ❌</strong></td><td>Family history of CAD · Age (Men >45, Women >55) · Male gender (earlier onset) · Race (higher in African Americans)</td><td class="ar-cell">التاريخ العائلي · السن (رجل >٤٥، امرأة >٥٥) · الجنس · العرق</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong style="color:var(--green);">Modifiable ✅</strong></td><td>Hyperlipidemia · Cigarette smoking & tobacco · Hypertension · Diabetes mellitus · Obesity · Physical inactivity</td><td class="ar-cell">فرط الدهون · تدخين · ارتفاع ضغط · سكري · سمنة · خمول بدني</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- 5. ANGINA -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-angina">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">💔</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">Angina Pectoris — Types</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">الذبحة الصدرية — الأنواع</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--red-light);color:var(--red);">5 TYPES</span>
    </div>
    <div class="angina-grid">
      <div class="angina-card"><div class="angina-head stable">✅ Stable Angina — الذبحة المستقرة</div><div class="angina-body">Predictable, consistent pain ON EXERTION. Relieved by REST and/or Nitroglycerin.<div class="ar">ألم متوقع عند المجهود. يخف بالراحة أو النيتروجليسرين.</div></div></div>
      <div class="angina-card"><div class="angina-head unstable">⚠️ Unstable Angina — ذبحة غير مستقرة (قبل الاحتشاء)</div><div class="angina-body">Increasing frequency and severity. <strong>NOT relieved by rest or nitroglycerin.</strong> = PRE-INFARCTION EMERGENCY!<div class="ar">تزداد تكراراً وشدةً. لا تخف بالراحة أو النيتروجليسرين = طارئة!</div></div></div>
      <div class="angina-card"><div class="angina-head variant">🌙 Variant (Prinzmetal) — الذبحة المتغيرة</div><div class="angina-body">Pain at REST caused by coronary artery <strong>vasospasm</strong>. Not triggered by exertion.<div class="ar">ألم أثناء الراحة بسبب تشنج الشرايين التاجية. لا تحتاج مجهوداً.</div></div></div>
      <div class="angina-card"><div class="angina-head silent">🔕 Silent Ischemia — الإقفار الصامت</div><div class="angina-body">ECG evidence of ischemia (ST changes) but patient reports <strong>NO PAIN</strong>.<div class="ar">تغيرات في رسم القلب (تغير ST) لكن المريض لا يشعر بأي ألم.</div></div></div>
      <div class="angina-card" style="grid-column:1/-1"><div class="angina-head intractable">😣 Intractable Angina — الذبحة المستعصية</div><div class="angina-body">Severe, <strong>incapacitating</strong> chest pain. Does NOT respond to standard treatment.<div class="ar">ألم صدري شديد يُعجز المريض. لا يستجيب للعلاج المعتاد.</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box gold" style="margin-top:13px;">
      <div class="def-en">⚡ <strong>Triggers:</strong> (1) Physical exertion → ↑ O₂ demand; (2) Cold exposure → vasoconstriction → ↑ BP; (3) Heavy meal → blood diverted to GI; (4) Stress/emotions → catecholamines → ↑ BP & HR.</div>
      <div class="def-ar">محفزات الذبحة: مجهود (↑ طلب O₂) · برد (تشنج أوعية) · وجبة دسمة (الدم للهضم) · توتر وانفعال (كاتيكولامين → ↑ ضغط ونبض).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box blue" style="margin-top:13px;">
      <div class="def-en"><strong>Angina Manifestations:</strong> Chest pain (mild indigestion → choking/heavy sensation) · Poorly localized, may radiate to neck, jaw, shoulders, left arm · Weakness/numbness in arms · SOB · Pallor · Diaphoresis · Dizziness · Nausea/vomiting.</div>
      <div class="def-ar">أعراض الذبحة: ألم صدر (خفيف → ثقيل/اختناق) · غير محدد يمتد للرقبة والفك والذراع الأيسر · ضعف/تنميل · ضيق تنفس · شحوب · تعرق · دوخة · غثيان.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 6. ACS -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-acs">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">🚨</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">Acute Coronary Syndrome (ACS) / MI</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">المتلازمة التاجية الحادة / احتشاء عضلة القلب</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--red-light);color:var(--red);">EMERGENCY</span>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box red">
      <div class="def-en"><strong>ACS = emergent situation:</strong> acute myocardial ischemia → <strong>myocardial death</strong> (necrosis) without prompt intervention. Also called: coronary occlusion, heart attack, myocardial infarction (MI).</div>
      <div class="def-ar"><strong>ACS = حالة طارئة:</strong> نقص تروية حاد للقلب → <strong>موت أنسجة القلب</strong> (نخر) بدون تدخل سريع. تُعرف أيضاً: احتشاء عضلة القلب، النوبة القلبية.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-card a"><h4>😣 ACS Symptoms</h4><ul class="care-list" style="margin-top:4px;"><li>Sudden chest pain (continues despite rest)</li><li>Shortness of breath (SOB)</li><li>Indigestion feeling</li><li>Nausea and vomiting</li><li>Anxiety and sense of doom</li><li>Cool, pale, moist skin</li><li>↑ HR & RR (sympathetic stimulation)</li></ul></div>
      <div class="col-card b"><h4>⚡ ACS Complications</h4><ul class="care-list" style="margin-top:4px;"><li>Acute pulmonary edema</li><li>Heart failure</li><li>Cardiogenic shock</li><li>Dysrhythmias (arrhythmias)</li><li>Cardiac arrest</li><li>Pericardial effusion + tamponade</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 7. ACS MANAGEMENT -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-acsmgmt">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">💊</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">ACS Early Management (EXAM!)</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">الإدارة المبكرة لـ ACS — امتحاني!</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--red-light);color:var(--red);">8 STEPS</span>
    </div>
    <div class="acs-steps">
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">①</div><div class="acs-step-en">12-lead ECG + History</div><div class="acs-step-detail">Primary diagnostic tools</div><div class="acs-step-ar">رسم قلب ١٢ وصلة</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">②</div><div class="acs-step-en">Aspirin 160–325 mg</div><div class="acs-step-detail">CHEWED — not swallowed whole</div><div class="acs-step-ar">أسبرين — مضغ!</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">③</div><div class="acs-step-en">Sublingual Nitroglycerin</div><div class="acs-step-detail">Vasodilator — ↓ ischemia</div><div class="acs-step-ar">نيتروجليسرين تحت اللسان</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">④</div><div class="acs-step-en">Morphine Sulfate</div><div class="acs-step-detail">Adequate analgesia</div><div class="acs-step-ar">مورفين — تخفيف الألم</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">⑤</div><div class="acs-step-en">O₂ Nasal Cannula</div><div class="acs-step-detail">↑ O₂ to myocardium</div><div class="acs-step-ar">أكسجين — قنية أنفية</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">⑥</div><div class="acs-step-en">IV Heparin</div><div class="acs-step-detail">Prevent further clotting</div><div class="acs-step-ar">هيبارين وريدي</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">⑦</div><div class="acs-step-en">Bed Rest</div><div class="acs-step-detail">Min 12–24 hours</div><div class="acs-step-ar">راحة ١٢–٢٤ ساعة</div></div>
      <div class="acs-step"><div class="acs-step-num">⑧</div><div class="acs-step-en">Cardiac Monitor</div><div class="acs-step-detail">Serial ECG monitoring</div><div class="acs-step-ar">مراقبة قلبية مستمرة</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="def-box gold" style="margin-top:13px;">
      <div class="def-en">🧠 <strong>Memory Aid:</strong> <em>ECG → Aspirin (CHEW!) → Nitro SL → Morphine → O₂ → Heparin → Bed rest → Monitor</em>. In intensive care: IV nitroglycerin continued 24–48 hrs + IV beta-blockers in initial hours.</div>
      <div class="def-ar">تذكّر: رسم → أسبرين (مضغ!) → نيتروجليسرين → مورفين → أكسجين → هيبارين → راحة → مراقبة. في العناية: نيتروجليسرين IV لمدة ٢٤–٤٨ ساعة + حاصرات بيتا IV.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 8. PREVENTION -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-prevention">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">🛡️</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">CAD Prevention Strategies</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">استراتيجيات الوقاية من CAD</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--green-light);color:var(--green);">PREVENTION</span>
    </div>
    <div class="care-grid">
      <div class="care-card"><h4>🥗 Cholesterol Control</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>TLC diet (low saturated fat, high soluble fiber)</li><li>Lipid-lowering medications (statins) if diet insufficient</li><li>Vegetarian diet: ↓ blood lipids, glucose, BMI, BP</li></ul></div>
      <div class="care-card"><h4>🏃 Physical Activity</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>Regular moderate exercise ↓ triglycerides</li><li>↓ CAD events and overall mortality</li><li>STOP if: chest pain, unusual SOB, dizziness, nausea, or lightheadedness</li></ul></div>
      <div class="care-card"><h4>🚭 Tobacco Cessation</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>Education and counseling</li><li>Support groups</li><li>Pharmacological aids (nicotine replacement)</li></ul></div>
      <div class="care-card"><h4>🩺 Diabetes Control</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>DM accelerates heart disease</li><li>65–75% of diabetic deaths are from CVD</li><li>Hyperglycemia → ↑ platelet aggregation → clots</li><li>Insulin/metformin improve endothelial function</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 9. NURSING CARE -->
  <div class="study-section" id="sec-nursing">
    <div class="study-section-header">
      <span class="study-section-icon">🩺</span>
      <div><div class="study-section-title">ACS Nursing Care Plan</div><div class="study-section-title-ar">خطة التمريض للمتلازمة التاجية الحادة</div></div>
      <span class="study-section-badge" style="background:var(--teal-light);color:var(--teal);">NURSING</span>
    </div>
    <div class="care-grid">
      <div class="care-card"><h4>📋 Nursing Diagnoses</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>Ineffective cardiac tissue perfusion r/t ↓ coronary blood flow</li><li>Risk for imbalanced fluid volume r/t inadequate intake</li><li>Anxiety related to cardiac event</li><li>Deficient knowledge about post-ACS self-care</li></ul></div>
      <div class="care-card"><h4>📊 Monitoring</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>Continuous cardiac monitoring (ECG)</li><li>Vital signs (BP, HR, RR, SpO₂)</li><li>Chest pain: PQRST assessment</li><li>Urine output (adequate perfusion)</li><li>Serial cardiac enzymes (troponin, CK-MB)</li></ul></div>
      <div class="care-card"><h4>💊 Interventions</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>Administer medications as ordered (sequence!)</li><li>Strict bed rest (min 12–24 hrs)</li><li>Oxygen therapy</li><li>IV access and fluid management</li><li>Calm, quiet environment (reduce anxiety)</li></ul></div>
      <div class="care-card"><h4>📚 Patient Education</h4><ul class="care-list"><li>Medication compliance (aspirin, statins, beta-blockers)</li><li>Activity resumption: gradually increase</li><li>Low-fat, low-cholesterol diet</li><li>Smoking cessation</li><li>When to call emergency: chest pain >15 min</li></ul></div>
    </div>
    <div class="crit-box" style="margin-top:13px;">
      <h4>🎯 KEY POINTS TO REMEMBER</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Heart has 3 layers: Endocardium · Myocardium (PUMP!) · Epicardium.</li>
        <li>Pericardial space = ~20 mL fluid (lubrication, reduces friction during systole).</li>
        <li>Coronary arteries are perfused during DIASTOLE only!</li>
        <li>Tachycardia (>100) → shortened diastole → ischemia risk!</li>
        <li>CAD = most prevalent cardiovascular disease in adults.</li>
        <li>Atherosclerosis = lipid + fibrous accumulation in arterial walls.</li>
        <li>Non-modifiable risk factors: age (M>45, F>55), family history, gender, race.</li>
        <li>Unstable angina: NOT relieved by rest/nitroglycerin = EMERGENCY!</li>
        <li>Variant (Prinzmetal) angina: at REST, due to VASOSPASM.</li>
        <li>Silent ischemia: ECG changes but NO pain (common in diabetics).</li>
        <li>ACS sequence: ECG → Aspirin (CHEW 160–325 mg) → Nitro SL → Morphine → O₂ → Heparin → Bed rest.</li>
        <li>ACS complications: pulmonary edema, heart failure, cardiogenic shock, cardiac arrest.</li>
        <li>Stop exercise if: chest pain, unusual SOB, dizziness, nausea, lightheadedness.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

